<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1576917-i-would-like-to-explore-this-author-but">I would like to explore this author, but heard Knots and Crosses is not his best. Is there another early in the series that would work as a good introduction to Inspector Rebus?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1576917'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F77490.Hide_and_Seek">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1576917-i-would-like-to-explore-this-author-but">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1576917-i-would-like-to-explore-this-author-but">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1416377-ian"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1442525573i/1416377._UX100_CR0,37,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1416377-ian">Ian</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I&apos;d say start with <i>The Black Book</i> it&apos;s the first in which Rebus moves into the real world and it introduces a number of characters who are regulars in<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I'd say start with <i>The Black Book</i> it's the first in which Rebus moves into the real world and it introduces a number of characters who are regulars in later novels. Rebus is also a more fully formed character than in the earlier books.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

