<div id="review_2339261945" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2339261945" />
    <a title="Lynn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17552047-lynn"><img alt="Lynn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1619529993p2/17552047.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2339261945?book_show_action=true">Mar 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lynn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lynn" href="/user/show/17552047-lynn">Lynn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2339261945" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer648370152344557767">I enjoyed this 2nd entry in the Inspector Rebus series. I have a lot more reading to do as I think there are 21 books in the series. <br/><br/>I am not going to write a synopsis as many have already done so. Instead I&apos;ll relate what I liked about the book and why I want to continue on with the series. First of all, I like the character of John Rebus. When he gets on a mission or case, he doesn&apos;t let go. I read in other reviews that his personality changes somewhat in upcoming books. I have also read that </span>
  <span id="freeText648370152344557767" style="display:none">I enjoyed this 2nd entry in the Inspector Rebus series. I have a lot more reading to do as I think there are 21 books in the series. <br /><br />I am not going to write a synopsis as many have already done so. Instead I'll relate what I liked about the book and why I want to continue on with the series. First of all, I like the character of John Rebus. When he gets on a mission or case, he doesn't let go. I read in other reviews that his personality changes somewhat in upcoming books. I have also read that the books just get better and better as they go along. Well, I liked this book very much so am looking forward to continuing in the series. <br /><br />Another part I liked was the location of Edinburgh . The book showed all the different sides of the city. (from the squats to the wealthy mansions) As I read I wondered what secondary characters in this book will be in the next book. I did like the character of Holmes. Hope he hangs in there and continues on with his police career. Rebus chose him for different tasks because he thought he wouldn't complain. Sometimes Inspector Rebus didn't treat him real well but it seemed he was gaining respect for him by the end of the book.<br /><br />The mystery was good. As the book developed, more and more was revealed. I didn't have it all figured out but I wasn't surprised as to who was behind the crimes. I am looking forward to continuing on with the series. I have some good reading ahead of me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="648370152344557767" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


