<div id="review_1965860033" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1965860033" />
    <a title="Jill Hutchinson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2222319-jill-hutchinson"><img alt="Jill Hutchinson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1304786753p2/2222319.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1965860033?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jill Hutchinson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jill Hutchinson" href="/user/show/2222319-jill-hutchinson">Jill Hutchinson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2222319-jill-hutchinson?shelf=mystery-police-procedural">mystery-police-procedural</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1965860033" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14529797743915211306">I think Rankin was still trying to develop the persona of John Rebus which is so strong in the later books in this long running series. But that is the fun of reading the early books in a series......seeing the protagonist change and get comfortable in his skin. I think the problem I had which kept me from giving a higher rating (I love the Rebus books) was the story itself. There was way too much going on around the overdose death of a local addict. Rebus has a feeling about it that says it is </span>
  <span id="freeText14529797743915211306" style="display:none">I think Rankin was still trying to develop the persona of John Rebus which is so strong in the later books in this long running series. But that is the fun of reading the early books in a series......seeing the protagonist change and get comfortable in his skin. I think the problem I had which kept me from giving a higher rating (I love the Rebus books) was the story itself. There was way too much going on around the overdose death of a local addict. Rebus has a feeling about it that says it is murder. Then the wild ride begins through dog fighting, gambling, sex clubs, rent boys and a few more things of which I lost track. There were more characters in this short book than are found in <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/656.War_and_Peace" title="War and Peace by Leo Tolstoy" rel="nofollow noopener">War and Peace</a>. Certainly not my favorite of the Rebus adventures.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14529797743915211306" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

