<div id="review_4068251033" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4068251033" />
    <a title="Bryan Brown" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17539226-bryan-brown"><img alt="Bryan Brown" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1480206005p2/17539226.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4068251033?book_show_action=true">Jun 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bryan Brown" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bryan Brown" href="/user/show/17539226-bryan-brown">Bryan Brown</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17539226-bryan-brown?shelf=mysteries">mysteries</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4068251033" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10468135729906642103">I started this book hopeful that the hero would have grown some after his first experience. This story picks up several months after the end of the last story, and it&apos;s immediately obvious that Rebus has improved his condition and life some. For one he&apos;s promoted to inspector, and he&apos;s managed to kick off some of the gloom and doom that was so heavy in the first book. <br/><br/>The local head of the police want Rebus to be the public face of an anti-drug campaign especially because his brother is in jail </span>
  <span id="freeText10468135729906642103" style="display:none">I started this book hopeful that the hero would have grown some after his first experience. This story picks up several months after the end of the last story, and it's immediately obvious that Rebus has improved his condition and life some. For one he's promoted to inspector, and he's managed to kick off some of the gloom and doom that was so heavy in the first book. <br /><br />The local head of the police want Rebus to be the public face of an anti-drug campaign especially because his brother is in jail on drug offence charges. He is ordered to "wrap up" his current case load and get ready to do this full time. <br /><br />But it is easier said than done. Rebus caught a homicide case the very morning he is told to wrap things up. Rebus avoids his new task by focusing on the murder of a junky in a bad part of town. But the more he delves into the death the stranger the case becomes. An abundance of clues are presented along with some red herrings. This was a very pleasant change from the previous book where no clues were revealed. <br /><br /><a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[If you are paying attention you can make a good guess at who killed the junkie. The other interesting thing about this mystery is the understanding Rebus gains on the sordid connections below the surface of the seemingly genteel upper crust. Their connections to the murder are discovered although not made public. Even Rebus ends up destroying evidence to avoid more harm to people he's connected with.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> <br /><br />All in all I'm encouraged by the direction the author's skill at mysteries is progressing along with the progression of the hero's personality. I'll keep reading this.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10468135729906642103" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

